race.comment: SUPERFLUOUS (1) was put aside after a couple of starts during a winter campaign and will resume at an easier level. He was third in a recent trial and will don the blinkers again for his return. He has the aid of a 3kg claim and should go close to winning this. COME ON EMMA (3) resumed with a fast finishing run for third at Ascot 17 days ago. She can settle closer to the pace this time from a superior gate, and her next win is not far away. Stick with her. LONDON'S RASCAL (10) has shown a lot of improvement since being tried in front. He led all the way to score by almost a length at Ascot 2 weeks ago, and from a good draw with only an extra 2kg to carry, he could take some pegging back again. CANTRIX (4) had a tough run fresh up and still kept on fighting hard to hold onto third here just over 3 weeks ago. She has some upside and can win a race like this. PYGMALION (7) has been racing well enough since leaving his maiden status at Northam in October. Include in all top 4 combos.
